{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-markdown-remark-js","path":"/community/community/community-cloud-sunset-how-to.md","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Operate First"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"87dba0e3-91c1-5af1-b74b-1c9c20799e06","html":"<h1 id=\"operate-first-community-cloud-sunset-how-to-notes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#operate-first-community-cloud-sunset-how-to-notes\" aria-label=\"operate first community cloud sunset how to notes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Operate First community cloud sunset how-to notes</h1>\n<h2 id=\"rosa\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#rosa\" aria-label=\"rosa permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>ROSA</h2>\n<ol class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>Obtain an AWS account, connected to a credit card for billing or provided with AWS cloud credits for Open Source projects.\nYou will need an AWS key to connect your OpenShift instance to.</li>\n<li>File a <a href=\"https://github.com/operate-first/community/issues/new?assignees=quaid%2C+cooktheryan&#x26;labels=area%2Fcommunity%2C+kind%2Fdocumentation%2C+kind%2Fonboarding&#x26;template=project-intake-or-migration-request.md&#x26;title=Project+Name+%28Intake%7CMigration%29+request\">migration issue here</a>. Tech lead Ryan Cook or a member of his team will work with you to use the no-cost ROSA tier being offered for these projects.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"nerc\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#nerc\" aria-label=\"nerc permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NERC</h2>\n<p><strong>Note: This is not a free-for-all offering, you must be associated with a participating institution for easier connection.</strong>\nIf you are not in a participating institution but are interested in the NERC, we will need to have a direct conversation about how to do that.\nYou can open a ticket with this question <a href=\"https://github.com/operate-first/community/issues/new\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Refer to the NERC <a href=\"https://nerc.mghpcc.org/user-guides/\">user guides</a> for the <a href=\"https://nerc-project.github.io/nerc-docs/get-started/user-onboarding-on-NERC/\">User Onboarding Process Overview</a> that explains the process and roles involved.\nThe <a href=\"https://nerc-project.github.io/nerc-docs/get-started/create-a-user-portal-account/\">User Account Types</a> document explains roles and getting an account.</p>\n<ol class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://regapp.mss.mghpcc.org/\">Request a NERC account</a>, picking the <strong>General User*</strong> account type.</li>\n<li>File a <a href=\"https://github.com/operate-first/community/issues/new?assignees=quaid%2C+cooktheryan&#x26;labels=area%2Fcommunity%2C+kind%2Fdocumentation%2C+kind%2Fonboarding&#x26;template=project-intake-or-migration-request.md&#x26;title=Project+Name+%28Intake%7CMigration%29+request\">migration issue here</a>.</li>\n<li>You will be put in contact with Red Hat’s primary lead for intaking projects to NERC, who will perform a standard interview and NERC intake process for you.</li>\n<li>If you discover in this process there is a service needed that is not yet available, we’ll work with you to look for solutions.</li>\n</ol>","fields":{"srcLink":"https://github.com/operate-first/community/blob/master/community-cloud-sunset-how-to.md"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Operate First community cloud sunset how-to","description":"How-to instructions for Operate First community cloud sunset activities","extraClasses":null,"banner":null}}},"pageContext":{"id":"87dba0e3-91c1-5af1-b74b-1c9c20799e06"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1764348645","2823140819","3000541721","3606484676"]}